sentences: Sa mine ajalehte ostma, ma võtan seni poes järjekorra ära.
Ma käin korraks ära, hoia mulle järjekorda!
context: The word 'järjekord' means queue or line in English. It refers to a sequence of people waiting for something, such as standing in line at a ticket counter. The term can also refer to the order or sequence of events, operations, or items in a series.
